'''Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine''' (おおさかやまぐちじんじゃ) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} located in {{jalink|Ōsaka (Kashiba City)||Ōsaka}} (Ōsaka), {{jalink|Kashiba City|Q696643}}, {{jalink|Nara Prefecture|Q131287}}.

=== Overview ===
The shrine is enshrined in the northeastern vicinity of {{jalink|Futakami Station|Q7034597}} on the {{jalink|Kintetsu Osaka Line|Q1052545}}.

Together with {{jalink|Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine (Anamushi, Kashiba City)|Q135069035|Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine}} in the Anamushi district, it is identified as the shrine that enshrined the Ōsaka deity mentioned in a dream oracle recorded in the 9th year of {{jalink|Emperor Sujin|Q333530}} in the {{jalink|Kojiki|Q813031}} and {{jalink|Nihon Shoki|Q813935}}: “With eight red shields and eight red halberds, enshrine the god of Sumisaka (Sumisaka-no-kami); with eight black shields and eight black halberds, enshrine the god of Ōsaka (Ōsaka-no-kami).” (Incidentally, the god of Sumisaka is identified with {{jalink|Sumisaka Shrine (Uda City)||Sumisaka Shrine}} in {{jalink|Uda City|Q863747}}.)<ref name="city-muse">[https://www.city.kashiba.lg.jp/uploaded/attachment/1655.pdf Ōsaka and Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine] - Kashiba City Futakami Mountain Museum</ref><ref name="pref-db">[https://www.pref.nara.jp/miryoku/ikasu-nara/bunkashigen/main00217.html Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine Main Hall, Sacred Statues and Treasure Items (Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine Main Hall, Sacred Statues and Treasure Items of Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine)] - Nara Prefecture Historical and Cultural Resources Database</ref>.

In addition, together with the Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine in the Anamushi district, it is considered a candidate shrine (ronsha) for Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine, one of the shrines listed in the {{jalink|List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province|Q11433427|List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province}}<ref name="city-muse"/><ref name="pref-db"/>.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{jalink|Ōyamatsumi-no-Mikoto}}
* {{jalink|Susanoo-no-Mikoto}}
* {{jalink|Kamioichihime-no-Mikoto}}

