Together with {{ill|lt=Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine (Anamushi, Kashiba City)|Q135069035|WD=Q135069035|lt=Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine}} in the Anamushi district, it is identified as the shrine that enshrined the Ōsaka deity mentioned in a dream oracle recorded in the 9th year of {{ill|lt=Emperor Sujin|Q333530|WD=Q333530}} in the {{ill|lt=Kojiki|Q813031|WD=Q813031}} and {{ill|lt=Nihon Shoki|Q813935|WD=Q813935}}: “With eight red shields and eight red halberds, enshrine the god of Sumisaka (Sumisaka-no-kami); with eight black shields and eight black halberds, enshrine the god of Ōsaka (Ōsaka-no-kami).” (Incidentally, the god of Sumisaka is identified with {{ill|lt=Sumisaka Shrine (Uda City)|UNKNOWN|WD=|lt=Sumisaka Shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Uda City|Q863747|WD=Q863747}}.)<ref name="city-muse">[https://www.city.kashiba.lg.jp/uploaded/attachment/1655.pdf Ōsaka and Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine] - Kashiba City Futakami Mountain Museum</ref><ref name="pref-db">[https://www.pref.nara.jp/miryoku/ikasu-nara/bunkashigen/main00217.html Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine Main Hall, Sacred Statues and Treasure Items (Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine Main Hall, Sacred Statues and Treasure Items of Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine)] - Nara Prefecture Historical and Cultural Resources Database</ref>.

