'''Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine''' (おおさかやまぐちじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} located in {{ill|lt=Ōsaka (Kashiba City)|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōsaka}} (Ōsaka), {{ill|lt=Kashiba City|Q696643|WD=Q696643}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|WD=Q131287}}.

=== Overview ===
The shrine is enshrined in the northeastern vicinity of {{ill|lt=Futakami Station|Q7034597|WD=Q7034597}} on the {{ill|lt=Kintetsu Osaka Line|Q1052545|WD=Q1052545}}.

Together with {{ill|lt=Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine (Anamushi, Kashiba City)|Q135069035|WD=Q135069035|lt=Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine}} in the Anamushi district, it is identified as the shrine that enshrined the Ōsaka deity mentioned in a dream oracle recorded in the 9th year of {{ill|lt=Emperor Sujin|Q333530|WD=Q333530}} in the {{ill|lt=Kojiki|Q813031|WD=Q813031}} and {{ill|lt=Nihon Shoki|Q813935|WD=Q813935}}: “With eight red shields and eight red halberds, enshrine the god of Sumisaka (Sumisaka-no-kami); with eight black shields and eight black halberds, enshrine the god of Ōsaka (Ōsaka-no-kami).” (Incidentally, the god of Sumisaka is identified with {{ill|lt=Sumisaka Shrine (Uda City)|UNKNOWN|lt=Sumisaka Shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Uda City|Q863747|WD=Q863747}}.)<ref name="city-muse">[https://www.city.kashiba.lg.jp/uploaded/attachment/1655.pdf Ōsaka and Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine] - Kashiba City Futakami Mountain Museum</ref><ref name="pref-db">[https://www.pref.nara.jp/miryoku/ikasu-nara/bunkashigen/main00217.html Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine Main Hall, Sacred Statues and Treasure Items (Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine Main Hall, Sacred Statues and Treasure Items of Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine)] - Nara Prefecture Historical and Cultural Resources Database</ref>.

In addition, together with the Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine in the Anamushi district, it is considered a candidate shrine (ronsha) for Ōsaka Yamaguchi Shrine, one of the shrines listed in the {{ill|lt=List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province|Q11433427|WD=Q11433427|lt=List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province}}<ref name="city-muse"/><ref name="pref-db"/>.

=== Enshrined deities ===
